---
import Sectionhead from "@components/sectionhead.astro";
---

<div id="vision" class="bg-white py-24 sm:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
          Whys of InfraGPT
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          A founder's perspective on the future of infrastructure management
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto text-gray-700 space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
          <p class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-900 mb-2">My core belief:</p>
          <p class="text-blue-800 italic">
            "In today's world, building and managing software shouldn't be a daunting task."
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <p class="text-lg">
          I've been managing infrastructure for a decade both as a developer and as a infrastructure engineer.
       I've maintained >99% uptime for large-scale systems
          and reduced production costs. At OkCredit I reduced cost of serving 2 million MAUs from ₹400,000 to ₹50,000 per day. Through this journey, 
          I've seen firsthand how hard it is to manage infrastructure for software teams.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Today's reality is overwhelming microservices, container orchestrators, multi-region deployments, 
          security compliance, and now the rise of "vibe coding". We are producing more code than ever.
           All of this lands hot in production, creating an urgent need for counterbalance.
        </p>
        
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">The Problem We're Solving</h3>
          <p class="text-amber-800">
            Instead of focusing on fixing production issues at 2AM or doing boring cost analysis, people should prioritize building 
            amazing user experiences and great features. DevOps expertise should be accessible and affordable, 
            not a privilege of well-funded teams.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Why AI Agents Are the Answer</h3>
        
        <p>
          The deterministic nature of infrastructure makes it perfect for AI agents. Unlike other domains,
          infrastructure problems have clear terminal states. We can determine when we've solved an issue with 
          confidence. This is what makes the approach viable.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Modern reasoning models can think step-by-step, breaking down complex problems into logical steps. 
          Combined with tools and context from your entire infrastructure graph who deployed what, when, 
          and why - agents can solve problems that traditionally required deep expertise.
        </p>
        
        <div>
          <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-10">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Example of workflows it enables</h4>
            <ul class="text-green-800 space-y-2">
              <li>Incident response without waking anyone at 2AM</li>
              <li>Automated infrastructure drift detection and PR generation</li>
              <li>Cost insights with every infrastructure change</li>
              <li>Continuous security monitoring and remediation</li>
              <li>Knowledge that improves with every problem solved</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-3">Success Metrics That Matter</h4>
            <ul class="text-purple-800 space-y-2">
              <li>Reduced MTTR (Mean Time To Resolution)</li>
              <li>Lower cloud bills month over month</li>
              <li>Higher deployment frequency</li>
              <li>No burnouts, and Engineers focusing on higher-value work</li>
              <li>Strong security posture</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">User Experience Is Everything</h3>
        
        <p>
          Developer primarily use Slack, Github and the terminal for their work.
         We’re building InfraGPT that it integrates directly with existing workflows. People 
          should be able agents in a way that feels natural. It's like having a agentic teammate. 
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Why OpenSource</h3>
        
        
        <p>
          We believe in the power of open source to drive innovation and adoption. By making InfraGPT open source, people know exactly what's running in their production environments.
          It ensures transparency and trust in how AI is applied to infrastructure. 
        </p>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">The Future as I think of it </h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Over time, agents will become the default for infrastructure management. Organizations will start 
            with cost optimization, move to incident response, and eventually automate the all repetitive, 
            tedious parts. A future where engineers create software while an AI quietly keeps production safe.


            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600" style="text-align: right;">
              — Priyanshu Jain, Founder
            </p>
          </p>
        </div>
    
      </div>
      
